0.body: Welcome to the Manic Monolith: Do It Yourself book! This book will teach you the basics of the level editor, tricks and tips, and the use of ALL the objects in the game! note The book and the game are still in heavy developement, expect some things to be slightly out of date...
0.title: Introduction

1.body: One of the first thing you will have to learn is how to use the level editor UI, so this subchapter will walk you through all the stuff you need to know before you start using the level editor.
1.title: Editor UI

10.body: Another very important element of the level editor, the property editor allows you to change an object properties, like size, position, color, etc...
10.title: Property Editor

103.body: A Vector3 value that determies the object's linear velocity. When either the X, Y or Z values are not 0, Mart's velocity will be affected by the object's velocity. The two most important interactions are as follow but others can happen depending on which values you input. Linear Velocity has the same direction as Mart's Velocity = More velocity WHILE standing on the object! Linear Velocity has the opposite direction as Mart's Velocity = Less velocity WHILE standing on the object!

116.body: An secret object has a Number Value as it child. When Mart touches this object, he gets teleported into the secret tied with the Number Value 's Value property. If mart touches this object while already in a secret, he gets sent back to the secret he first went through.
116.title: Secret

117.body: This object has a Number Value as its child, this Number Value , stores a value ranging from 1 to 3, this value must be unique between all secrets in the main level.

120.body: Signs have the same properties and behaviour of Studs , but they can have text.
120.title: Sign

121.body: Every Sign has 3 children: A String Value named "Text": Contains the text that will be shown when the level is played. A String Value named "Font": Contains the font that will be used for the text in the Sign, if the font doesn't exist, the sign won't render its text, instead it will show: "Unknown font (invalid font will be shown here)!" All valid fonts are listed in this roblox documentation page A Color Value named "Text Color": Contains the color that the text will use when the level is played.
121.title: Remarks

81.body: Impulse Triggers are objects which apply a set amount of impulse to any object that touches it.
81.title: Impulse Trigger

82.body: All Impulse Triggers have two children: A Vector 3 Value named "Impulse Direction": This child stores the impulse direction of the trigger, a value of 0, 15, 0 will apply impulse to any object in a upwards direction. A Number Value named "Impulse Force": This child stores the force of the impulse, higher numbers makes this trigger apply stronger impulses on objects. However you can add those respective objects in order to modify the Impulse Trigger's behavior ( remember, you have to add those objects to the Impulse Trigger yourself. They are optional. ): A Number Value named "Debounce Timer": This child stores the amount of seconds that the Impulse Trigger needs to apply another impulse (A.K.A: Cooldown) A String Value named "Sound ID": This child stores a sound ID that will be played then the Impulse Trigger gets activated by something.
82.title: Remarks
